1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,251
Here is a psychological principle that is worth listening to repeatedly until it absolutely saturates you.

2
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:10,930
To think confidently, act confidently.

3
00:00:11,521 --> 00:00:17,970
The great psychologist, Dr. George W. Crane, said in his famous book, Applied Psychology,

4
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:22,771
remember, motions are the precursors of emotions.

5
00:00:23,041 --> 00:00:28,851
You can't control the latter directly, but only through your choice of motions or actions.

6
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:38,291
To avoid this all-too-common tragedy, marital difficulties and misunderstandings, become aware of the true psychological facts.

7
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:44,930
Go through the proper motions each day, and you'll soon begin to feel the corresponding emotions.

8
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:50,691
Just be sure you and your mate go through those motions of dates and kisses,

9
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:59,171
the phrasing of sincere daily compliments, plus the many other little courtesies, and you need not worry about the emotion of love.

10
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:03,890
You can't act devoted for very long without feeling devoted.

11
00:01:04,561 --> 00:01:10,450
Psychologists tell us we can change our attitudes by changing our physical actions.

12
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:16,450
For example, you actually feel more like smiling if you make yourself smile.

13
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:21,890
You feel more superior when you make yourself stand tall than when you slouch.

14
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:28,930
On the negative side, frown a really bitter frown and see if you don't feel more like frowning.

15
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:34,450
It is easy to prove that managed motions can change emotions.

16
00:01:34,561 --> 00:01:43,970
People who are shy in introducing themselves can replace this timidity with confidence just by taking three simple actions simultaneously.

17
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:48,691
First, reach for the other person's hand and clasp it warmly.

18
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:51,651
Second, look directly at the other person.

19
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:55,251
And third, say, I'm very glad to know you.

20
00:01:55,840 --> 00:02:01,571
These three simple actions automatically and instantaneously banish shyness.

21
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:05,010
Confident action produces confident thinking.

22
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:09,410
So, to think confidently, act confidently.

23
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:12,050
Act the way you want to feel.

24
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:15,651
Here are five confidence building exercises.

